<br>
<p>I've got all the 1st ed. products, and a few from LRG, I never really had a hard time getting new players into Earthdawn, no more at least than any other rpg, and alot less then some.  In fact it took off quite well with new players.<p></p>I also enjoyed the sourcebooks and the way they were laid out from character perspectives, the only exception being Throal area book was a hard read.<p></p>The problem I always had was finding people, it's easy to find roleplayers familiar with D&amp;D or the World of Darkness, but even alot of people in game stores were rather unfamiliar with Earthdawn, I agree with the posts saying it needs better word of mouth and demos in stores and at game/geek fests...<p></p>well, there's my spiel,<p></p>Vaughn, SLC,Ut</p>
